The article is a speech given by the First Lady of the United States, Jill Biden, at the flag-raising ceremony of the United States as a member state of UNESCO. She highlights the importance of global collaboration and peace, and discusses the commitment of the United States to rebuild broken systems and fortify institutions. She emphasizes the need for collective action to address challenges such as climate change, poverty, and human rights violations. The speech also focuses on the power of education to shape the future and empower young people to make a difference. Biden shares personal stories of individuals who have been positively impacted by education and emphasizes the role of UNESCO in spreading ideas, preserving history, and promoting understanding among cultures. She concludes by urging the audience to empower the next generation and work together to create a better future.